section_text: 18 1 The  Corn Returns Act, 1882, as amended by the  Corn Sales Act, 1921, shall have effect subject to the amendments set out in the Third Schedule to this Act, being amendments made for the purpose of — a removing the limits as to the number of towns to which the said Act is applicable; b abolishing the office of inspector of corn returns; and c providing for certain other matters of minor importance. 2 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
24 This Act may be cited as the Agriculture (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act, 1943.
